oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Memorial card, envelope and other material from H. F. Wendell & Co.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A portrait format printed card with the depiction of an American soldier at "port arms" in the lower left quarter with flag above at the upper left. An image of the Statue of Liberty is in the upper right with "PVT. FRANK M. RING/ Died Oct. 9, 1918./ From Wounds While Serving/As an Infantryman with American Expeditionary Forces." centered between. Other items include envelope and materials from H. F. Wendell & Co.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
